Russia sees push for return of official censorship
description: As the Kremlin increasingly restricts the flow of ideas, those nostalgic for the USSR are calling for the reinstatement of the state body that once decided what could and could not be published. They argue that entrusting this job 'to professionals rather than bureaucrats' would protect against arbitrariness.

headline: Trump says Epstein 'stole' young women from Mar-a-Lago spa, including Virginia Giuffre
description: Aboard Air Force One while returning from Scotland on Tuesday, Trump said he was upset that the late financier, who died by suicide in a NYC prison while awaiting trial on sex trafficking charges in 2019, was 'taking people who worked for me.'

headline: Cybèle Idelot's Ile-de-France adventure: from Hollywood childhood to kitchen gardens
description: 'Chefs' gardens' (1/5). The 50-year-old chef transformed a former coaching inn in Yvelines, just outside of Paris, into a domain that now welcomes guests to bed-and-breakfast rooms, a bistronomic restaurant, and above all, a vegetable garden that allows the restaurant to be self-sufficient.

headline: 'In the West Berlin squats, we argued but lived together': Karin Wieland, political rebel
description: 'Being 20 in West Berlin' (2/6). In the late 1970s, Karin Wieland fled her small German town to live communally in an abandoned building in Kreuzberg, throwing herself into every cause of the era.

description: 'Being 20 in West Berlin' (1/6). The actor, writer, translator, and photographer, a figure of Germany's artistic and intellectual scene, arrived in the walled-in city in the early 1970s. He never left, drawn by a vibrancy that set West Berlin apart from the rest of the Federal Republic of Germany at the time.

headline: Letters from prisoners held in solitary confinement: 'I feel like becoming violent again'
description: Le Monde asked five prisoners and a former inmate – the armed robber Rédoine Faïd, four drug traffickers, and a radicalized Islamist – to recount daily life in solitary confinement.
byline: Grégoire Biseau,  Lucie Soullier and  Thomas Saintourens

headline: Initial tariff impacts painful for auto, textile and chemical industries
